When attaching a screenshot, the dialog that pops up does not show the buttons at the bottom and entering "return" does not perform the highlighted action.

This is observed when viewing the browser windows on smaller screens, i.e., smaller resolutions. A workaround has been to zoom out or move across monitors where resolution available is higher, but it would be nice if the screen could auto-scale to support this such that visibility of the buttons is always available.

We understand that this is not a bug - just making a suggestion in case this is possible to address.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-47609].
  {panel}

Currently I get a lot of e-mails for small changes of the same ticket. It would be very helpful to see those e-mails as a conversation (thread) in GMail or Outlook or Thunderbird. I saw a tip in the answers forum to set the template to include RE: in the subject. however that is not sufficient if you change the subject based on for example status transitions.

A much better and robust solution would be to set the in-reply-to header to the ticket ID or something else that is constant to the ticket.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-47605].
